'''Cláudio Luiz Lottenberg''' (Born on September 6, 1960 in [[Sao Paulo]], Brazil) is a Brazilian [[physician]], [[executive]] and [[politician]]. He has a master’s and medical degree in [[Ophthalmology]] from Escola Paulista de Medicina – UNIFESP (Federal University of São Paulo).<ref>Menorah 2008  580-591 "Bis O paulistano Cláudio Luiz Lottenberg - médico oftalmologista - deu início ao terceiro mandato consecutivo como presidente da Sociedade Beneficente Israelita Brasileira Albert Einstein, mantenedora do hospital e dos institutos Israelita de ..."</ref> He is the second child of industrialist Marcos Lottenberg and grandson of Dr. Simão Lottenberg. All three generations are associated with the [[Hospital Israelita Albert Einstein]].<ref>''Who's who in Brazil''   1970 p970 "Son of late Simão Lottenberg and Clara Lottenberg. Married Cecília Lottenberg. Three children: Simão Augusto, Cláudio Luiz and Eliana Regina. Educated at the Economics Faculty of the Fundação Alvares Pentea do (1945)."</ref>

== Education ==
Dr. Lottenberg graduated with a medical degree in 1984 from the Escola Paulista de Medicina da Universidade Federal de Sao Paulo (UNIFESP).  In 1987 he completed a medical residency in [[Ophthalmology]].  After the completion of his Ophthalmology residency he received a masters degree in Ophthalmology and in 1994 he completed a doctorate in Ophthalmology, both from the Universidade Federal de Sao Paulo.

== Academic career ==
He served as an Assistant Professor in the Ophthalmology Graduation Course at the [[Universidade Federal de São Paulo]] and an Associate Professor at [[IBMEC]] (International Business and Management Education Centre) in the MBA Health Care Management program.

== Business and Political Career ==
Dr. Lottenberg is currently serving as the Chairman and President of [http://www.einstein.br/Paginas/home.aspx Sociedade Beneficente Israelita Brasileira Hospital Albert Einstein] holding this position since 2001 (Albert Einstein was the first hospital to be accreditted by the [[Joint Commission]] outside the USA and is currently ranked as the number one hospital in Latin America by “America Economia”).  During Dr. Lottenberg´s tenure, Hospital Albert Einstein has grown three fold in revenue and in assets.  Since 2008 Dr. Lottenberg also has served as president of the [http://www.conib.org.br/ Jewish Confederation of Brazil (CONIB)]. 

He was Secretary of Health of the City of [[Sao Paulo]] in 2005 during the government of [[Jose Serra]]. Dr. Lottenberg is the President of the [http://www.bloss.com.br/site/ Sociedade Brasileira de Laser e Cirurgia em Oftalmologia] (Brazilian Laser Ophthalmology Surgical Society - BLOSS) – term 2008/10.

== Writing career ==
Dr. Lottenberg is the author of several medical papers, and co-author of four books in Ophthalmology. He is the author of the book “[http://www.hospitalar.com/livros/liv1317.html A Saúde Brasileira pode dar Certo]” (Healthcare in Brazil can be fixed) published by Atheneu Publishing Company, 1st. Edition December, 2006. Dr. Lottenberg is frequently invited to give his opinion in articles about health and healthcare.

== Activities ==
He has served as counselor in many scientific, technical and public health boards, including: 
* The Joint Comission Intetrnational Committee
* The World Council for VISX refractive surgical procedures
* Conselho Nacional de Segurança Alimentar – CONSEA (The National Food and Nutritional Security Council) under the leadership of President [[Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva]]
* Advisory Board Foundation for Minor’s Well-Being in the State of Sao Paulo – FEBEM
* Advisory Board of the Association of Sales and Marketing Professionals of Brazil
* Advisory Board of the Charitable and Cultural B’nai B’rith Association, the Council of CNU - Brasil - Conversando com as Nações Unidas (Talking to the United Nations) 
* Scientific Commission of the Brazilian Medical Association’s Continuing Medical Education Program, COMSAUDE - Committee on Health Productive Chain 
* Brazilian Chapter of Israel Medical Association 
* Advisor to the Fundação Nacional da Qualidade – FNQ (National Quality Foundation)
* Member of  COPS - Council of the Political and Social Council- Associação Comercial de São Paulo (Commercial Association of Sao Paulo).

